extendedInfo.description: *** REQUIRES UP WRISTBAND TO USE THIS APP ***UP is a system, wristband + app, that tracks how you sleep, move and eat 24/7 so you can know yourself better, make smarter choices and feel your best.* Track your sleep & physical activity* Log your food & drink & track nutritional info* Get insights to help you set & achieve your goals* Set Smart Sleep Alarms to wake up refreshed* Set Idle Alerts to remind you to move* Team up with friends in the app and live better together* Supported languages: English, Spanish, Dutch, French, German, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese (Brazilian), Russian, Simplified Chinese and Traditional ChineseTRACK YOUR SLEEPHours slept, deep vs. light sleep, how long it took you to fall asleep and how many times you woke up.TRACK YOUR ACTIVITYSteps, distance, calories burned and time spent active vs. idle.LOG YOUR FOOD & DRINKLog what you eat and drink and get as detailed as you want. Take a photo of your food, scan a barcode, browse the UP image gallery or search the ingredient database. UP also helps you track calories, fats, carbohydrates, protein, sugar, fiber and sodium.GAIN INSIGHTUP simply and beautifully visualizes your information so, at a glance, you can understand the meaning behind your data. UP also delivers personalized insights and clear, actionable tips to help you achieve your goals. TAKE ACTIONUP helps you set daily goals and tracks your progress over time. It also lets you set helpful alarms and reminders. You can set multiple Smart Alarms to silently wake you at the ideal moment in your sleep cycle to help you wake up feeling refreshed. You can also set Idle Alerts to remind you to move when youâve been sitting too long.UP PLATFORMConnect UP with your favorite apps to complement your UP experience. Select from a variety of apps to seamlessly integrate new data into your feed, lifeline, and trends. You can also share your data from UP to the integrated apps to make those experiences even better.UP WRISTBAND* Required to use the UP by Jawbone app* Designed to be worn 24/7* Features advanced motion sensor technology* Up to 10 days of battery life between charges* Available in multiple colors & sizes (S, M, L)Check out jawbone.com/up/devices for a list of supported devices.

reviews.title: Used to work well
reviews.comment: Worked well on my gnex and my wife\'s razr. Got new phones and now it won\'t sync on either of them.  Followed support on the website still no luck. Guess I now have 250 dollars of colorful paperweights.  Going back to fitbit.  I noticed on the UP website this is common on android where these won\'t sync.     UPDATE: I DID EMAIL YOUR SUPPORT BEFORE WRITING THIS REVIEW< THEY DID NOT READ MY EMAIL AND WERE NOT HELPFUL AT ALL.  Thank you for posting canned responses and sending me robo emails instructing me to do the steps I already stated I had done.  Also for the record, JAWBONE suggested that if the new phones don\'t work with the Jawbone or app that I should just borrow a friends phone whenever I want to sync my device.  That is an awesome suggestion, don\'t use your $700 phone to sync your $150 dollar device.  Go find a friend with another phone and sync with his phone!!!!! Great advice Jawbone I will be sure to do that.  I own a lot of Jawbone products and after this fiasco will not be purchasing or recommending anymore.
reviews.author: Samuel Remp

reviews.title: can be better
reviews.comment: could u provide us a BMI calculator? its not gotta be hard is it?  i am sure that lots of JAWBONE UP user wanna lose weight, then why not an achievements list? it will definitely be motivative! hope that we can have a rich-in-content app soon <3
reviews.author: Debby Mo

reviews.title: Not perfect.
reviews.comment: This app does what I need.  Problems: syncing takes me 2-3 tries, readjusting the band, unplugging etc. Not as responsive as iOS version. Why can\'t we input distance of our run manually?  Additional thoughts: as extra incentive, add a leveling system, every 10k steps is x amount of exp etc. add fitocracy support!
reviews.author: Sean Sunyoto

reviews.title: Sync very slow
reviews.comment: The sync process is very slow when compare to ios version. Also I cannot add any comment on activity or sleep, there is no send button.
reviews.author: N. Nuntachit

reviews.title: WAS a 5 star app \'til now...
reviews.comment: All my workouts I timed WERE syncing right until the past 2 days. My past two timed workouts, steps for the day, and nights sleep didn\'t get logged in. Even after I forced closed the app, restarted my phone, made sure my battery wasn\'t dead (which is at 50%), and checked to see if I had the most recent version of the app. FIX THIS PLEASE AND IT WILL BE CHANGED TO WHAT IT DESERVES, 5 STAR.
reviews.author: Carl Magno

reviews.title: S4 has a better exercising tracking
reviews.comment: 2 hours of cycling, 8 minutes to sync to phone; 300 steps recorded!! Is this how this Up supposed to work? ....also, how can the calories be calculated in an exercise program without a heart rate? Is it too hard to incorporate a heart rate monitor to the bracelet?
reviews.author: Wally Ilt

reviews.title: Bugs and not polished
reviews.comment: There are a lot of things missing compared to thr iOS version. And thr bug with the syncing is just the worst
reviews.author: Dimo Trifonov

reviews.title: Trying it out
reviews.comment: I like the tips I wish you could  get more involved when you open the tips also I wish you could break down the day into hour segments so you could see how many step you took during a certain time frame I am still testing it out seeing if I will keep it or not and I also have syncing issue with the app
reviews.author: David Espinoza

reviews.title: band doesn\'t unlock on my phone...
reviews.comment: I got my band on Friday and it just won\'t be unlocked by my HTC One X (4.1.)... very disappointing. Tried it on HTC One and and Iphone 4 and it works there. All specs on my phone say it should work, but it\'s not the case. Contacted Jawbone, and posted on their forum, but they only don\'t have a solution the trick with volume and sound beats didn\'t do it either. I hope this will be fixed soon, otherwise I\'ll have to return the band.
reviews.author: Antonina Kuzovatova

reviews.title: why is it incompatible with my N7?!?!
reviews.comment: I don\'t have another device I can synchronise with! Cmon jawbone, this needs sorting PDQ

reviews.title: Crap
reviews.comment: Mine and two of my friends just stop working after about  three weeks. Software is no good if the hardware doesn\'t work..  Update.... Still crap and still don\'t work. Crap crap crap

reviews.title: No longer works
reviews.comment: Galaxy Nexus. I\'ve gone through two bands now. The first just died. Tried charging it and got nothing. My second band no longer syncs. I\'ve called the support line and gone through the steps, but no luck. No longer pleased w/ up band.

reviews.title: Sync needs to be fixed on Android 4.3
reviews.comment: Love the app. Sync seems to work again on my Nexus 4 since the recent minor Android update, although sometimes it needs a second try.
reviews.author: Andreas Alfons

reviews.title: Not working on HTC one X
reviews.comment: I have read the forums and tried everything there but the band still won\'t unlock. Very disappointed especially since the price is a premium. Please find a way to fix this asap or at least have a workaround working since some people apparently succeeded with this device.
reviews.author: Jason Hugh Untario

reviews.title: Would give five stars if...
reviews.comment: I would give it five stars if you could expand the trends section. For example I would like to see if I burn more if I eat breakfast vs not eating breakfast. I have mine synced with Myfitnesspal. The trends have been showing a lot of good data for me but lets see more!
reviews.author: Daniel Monts

reviews.title: Love my UP Band and the app
reviews.comment: The bar code reader is awesome for tracking my food with my phone camera, and I like that you already have most recognized food brands in the database. My favorite feature is the sleep tracker. Just tracking how much I sleep is helping me be more intentional about getting to bed earlier. Visuals are beautiful and I\'ve never had it crash on me.
reviews.author: Josue Sierra

reviews.title: Wont sync with Moto X
reviews.comment: Used to work perfect with my Nexus 4, but now, Moto X doesnt detect the band. Please fix.
reviews.author: F\303\252 von Christian

reviews.title: Ups and downs
reviews.comment: My interest my jawbone up band rises and falls very quickly. Some days it\'s great some days I could care less. Eventually you get used to the alarm feature on the band and you miss your alarm some days.
reviews.author: Anis Ali

reviews.title: App good, band not
reviews.comment: Band lasted less than a week before the battery died and wouldn\'t charge. Now waiting for my replacement to come.
reviews.author: Ruth Gullotta

reviews.title: Very bad android support (htc one x)
reviews.comment: I\'m very dissapointed in jawbone for advertising android support and not giving it. Can\'t do anything with it on my phone, no unlocking and obviously no syncing. Tried everything..  I bought this band because I\'m drawn to it by it\'s design and I\'d like to see statistics about my everyday moving. Too bad jawbone didn\'t deliver.   Better score when android is properly supported.
reviews.author: Sjors van Swaay
